==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tartarus
<hw>Tar"ta*rus</hw> <pr>(t⟦aum⟧r"t⟦adot⟧*r⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>prop.
n.</pos> <ety>[L., from Gr. <grk>Ta`rtaros</grk>.]</ety> <fld>(Class.
Myth.)</fld> <def>The infernal regions, described in the Iliad as
situated as far below Hades as heaven is above the earth, and by later
writers as the place of punishment for the spirits of the wicked. By the
later poets, also, the name is often used synonymously with
<altname>Hades</altname>, or the Lower World in general.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tartary</ent>⟦br⟧
